# x402 Server Integration

Add payment acceptance to any HTTP server with one middleware call. This integrates the [[ethereum/x402]] protocol into your server. You will need a [[ethereum/wallets]] to receive payments.

## Express

```typescript
import express from "express";
import { paymentMiddleware } from "@x402/express";

const app = express();

app.use(
  paymentMiddleware({
    "GET /weather": {
      price: "$0.01",
      network: "base",
      config: {
        description: "Weather data",
      },
    },
  }, {
    walletAddress: process.env.WALLET_ADDRESS,
    facilitatorUrl: "https://x402.org/facilitator",
  })
);

app.get("/weather", (req, res) => {
  res.json({ temp: 72, unit: "F" });
});

app.listen(3000);
```

## Hono

```typescript
import { Hono } from "hono";
import { paymentMiddleware } from "@x402/hono";

const app = new Hono();

app.use(
  "/data/*",
  paymentMiddleware({
    "GET /data/premium": {
      price: "$0.05",
      network: "base",
      config: { description: "Premium data access" },
    },
  }, {
    walletAddress: process.env.WALLET_ADDRESS,
    facilitatorUrl: "https://x402.org/facilitator",
  })
);
```

## How It Works

1. Middleware intercepts requests matching configured routes
2. If no `PAYMENT-SIGNATURE` header → respond HTTP 402 with `PAYMENT-REQUIRED` header
3. If header present → forward to facilitator `/verify` endpoint
4. If verification passes → run the route handler, then call facilitator `/settle`
5. Return 200 with resource + `PAYMENT-RESPONSE` header

See [[ethereum/x402#protocol-flow]] for the full sequence diagram and [[ethereum/x402#facilitator]] for details on how the facilitator verifies and settles.

## Configuration

The route map defines which endpoints require payment:

```typescript
{
  "METHOD /path": {
    price: "$0.01",          // USD amount (converted to token decimals)
    network: "base",         // Target chain
    config: {
      description: "...",    // Human-readable description
    },
  },
}
```

Global options:
- `walletAddress` — your receiving wallet address
- `facilitatorUrl` — facilitator endpoint (default: CDP facilitator)

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `WALLET_ADDRESS` | Address to receive payments |
| `FACILITATOR_URL` | Facilitator endpoint (optional, defaults to CDP) |
